  "title": "DBS Phantom Recordings",
  "description": "This dataset comprises MEG recordings from a CTF phantom system used to evaluate and compare deep brain stimulation (DBS) artifact rejection methods. The phantom recordings capture stimulation reference signals, movement triggers, and dipole activity to systematically assess the performance of various artifact rejection techniques in MEG data contaminated by DBS-related artifacts.",
  "methods_description": "MEG recordings were acquired using a CTF phantom system. Stimulation reference signals were captured via EEG001, movement triggers via UPPT001, and dipole activity via HADC006. The dataset was used to evaluate comparative performance of DBS artifact rejection methods.",
